This installation describes how to setup ODBRS on RHEL/CentOS.

1. Install apache.
2. Install python.
3. Install oracle instantclient basic and devel from repository or oracle web site.
4. Install pip.
5. Install cx_oracle library for python.
6. Create /var/www/cgi-bin/odbrs directory.
7. Copy the files from src folder to /var/www/cgi-bin/odbrs.
8. Set 755 permission to all .py and *.sh files and 666 to connections.ini in /var/www/cgi-bin/odbrs.
9. Copy odbrs.conf to /etc/httpd/conf.d
10. Create login and password "htpasswd -c /var/www/cgi-bin/odbrs/.htpasswd username".
11. Configure apache with support of ssl.
12. Restart apache.
13. Open the browser and connect to ODBRS https://youripaddress/odbrs/web.py?.
